label.value: spindle collapse during meiotic prometaphase I

value.value: A cell phenotype in which a short spindle assembles during the first meiotic nuclear division, and may begin elongation, but does not elongate normally or completely, and collapses during prometaphase I. Upon collapse the spindle may break or shrink.

label.value: spindle regression during meiosis I

value.value: A cell phenotype in which a short spindle assembles during the first meiotic nuclear division, and may begin elongation, but then become shorter instead of continuing or resuming elongation.

label.value: multiple spindles during meiosis I

value.value: A physical cellular phenotype in which a cell contains more than one meiotic spindle during the first meiotic nuclear division.

label.value: abolished mitotic spindle formation phase II

value.value: A physical cellular phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which phase II of mitotic spindle assembly does not occur. During phase II, the spindle is normally maintained at a constant length during mitotic metaphase.

label.value: short meiotic spindle during metaphase I

value.value: A physical cellular phenotype in which the spindle is shorter than normal during metaphase of meiosis I.

label.value: abnormal homologous chromosome segregation with collapsed spindle

value.value: A cell phenotype in which homologous chromosome segregation is abnormal, and the meiotic spindle collapses.

label.value: normal protein localization to new mitotic spindle pole body during anaphase

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the localization of a protein to the new mitotic spindle pole body is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type) during anaphase.

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: increased duration of mitotic sister chromatid cohesion

value.value: A cellular process phenotype in which mitotic sister chromatid cohesion lasts longer than normal, continuing into anaphase of mitosis.

label.value: increased duration of meiotic sister chromatid cohesion at centromere during meiosis I

value.value: A cellular process phenotype in which cohesion between sister chromatids lasts longer than normal in centromeric regions, continuing into anaphase of the first meiotic nuclear division.

label.value: decreased protein localization to kinetochore during meiotic prophase II

value.value: A cell phenotype in which the localization of a protein to the kinetochore of a chromosome is decreased during prophase of the second meiotic nuclear division.

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: normal protein phosphorylation during mitotic G2/M transition

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the phosphorylation of one or more specific proteins is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type) during the G2/M phase transition of the mitotic cell cycle.

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: abnormal phosphatidate cytidylyltransferase activity

value.value: A molecular function phenotype in which the observed rate of phosphatidate cytidylyltransferase activity is abnormal.

label.value: decreased phosphatidate cytidylyltransferase activity

value.value: A molecular function phenotype in which the observed rate of phosphatidate cytidylyltransferase activity is decreased.

label.value: enlarged lipid droplets surrounded by endoplasmic reticulum

value.value: A physical cellular phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which lipid droplets are larger than normal, and are surrounded by endoplasmic reticulum. Fewer droplets than normal may be present.

label.value: abnormal protein level oscillation during mitotic cell cycle

value.value: A gene expression phenotype in which protein levels that normally vary over the course of the mitotic cell cycle do not vary, or change in a pattern different from normal. Total protein or a specific protein may be affected.

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: abolished protein level oscillation during mitotic cell cycle

value.value: A gene expression phenotype in which protein levels that normally vary over the course of the mitotic cell cycle do not vary. Total protein or a specific protein may be affected.

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: decreased thiabendazole binding

value.value: A molecular function phenotype in which occurrence of thiabendazole binding by a gene product (usually a protein) in a mutant is decreased. The affected gene product may be encoded by the mutated gene, or by a different gene.

label.value: abnormal heterochromatin tethering at nuclear periphery

value.value: A cellular process phenotype in which heterochromatin tethering at the nuclear periphery is abnormal. Normally, heterochromatic parts of chromosomes, such as centromeres and telomeres, are maintained at the nuclear periphery by tethering to the nuclear envelope during all or part of the cell cycle.

label.value: increased heterochromatin tethering at nuclear periphery during mitosis

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which heterochromatin tethering at the nuclear periphery persists after the onset of mitosis. Normally, heterochromatic parts of chromosomes, such as centromeres and telomeres, are maintained at the nuclear periphery during interphase and released during mitosis.

label.value: increased telomere tethering at nuclear periphery during mitosis

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which telomere tethering at the nuclear periphery persists after the onset of mitosis. Normally, telomeres are maintained at the nuclear periphery during interphase and released during mitosis.

label.value: abnormally clustered protein localization to nuclear envelope

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which a protein is abnormally localized to one or more large clusters in the nuclear envelope. The protein may normally be distributed evenly in the nuclear envelope.

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: delayed onset of mitotic nuclear membrane reassembly

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which reformation of the nuclear envelope after mitotic nuclear division begins later than normal.

label.value: abnormal hyphal growth

value.value: A phenotype in which any aspect of hyphal growth is abnormal.

label.value: increased invasive hyphal growth

value.value: A phenotype in which fission yeast forms hyphae that invade the growth medium to a greater extent than normal. Invasively growing cells are wash-resistant when cultured in agar solid medium for several days.

label.value: increased hyphal length

value.value: A phenotype in which hyphae are longer than normal.

label.value: decreased hyphal length

value.value: A phenotype in which hyphae are shorter than normal.

label.value: increased hyphal branching

value.value: A phenotype in which hyphae form more branched filaments than normal.

label.value: decreased hyphal branching

value.value: A phenotype in which hyphae form fewer branched filaments than normal.

label.value: increased mycelial expansion

value.value: A phenotype in which the mycelium formed by fission yeast undergoing hyphal growth covers a larger area than normal.

label.value: decreased mycelial expansion

value.value: A phenotype in which the mycelium formed by fission yeast undergoing hyphal growth covers a smaller area than normal.

label.value: delayed onset of hyphal transition

value.value: A phenotype in which the transition from yeast-form to hyphal growth begins later than normal.

label.value: abolished hyphal transition

value.value: A phenotype in which the transition from yeast-form to hyphal growth does not occur under conditions that normally induce it.

label.value: abolished geometry scaling

value.value: A cell phenotype in which cellular geometry scaling, by which cells normally maintain a fairly constant length:diameter (width) ratio upon changes in cell volume, does not occur.

label.value: decreased protein localization to protein aggregate center

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the localization of a protein to protein aggregate centers is decreased. Protein aggregate centers are composed of chaperones and misfolded proteins, and are reversibly formed in the nucleus and cytosol to shield thermosensitive proteins from degradation until conditions allow disaggregation and refolding.

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: abnormal cell cycle arrest at meiotic G2/MI transition

value.value: A cellular process phenotype in which progression through the meiotic cell cycle is arrested at the G2/MI phase transition. Cells arrested at the G2/MI transition down-even in the presence of nutrients, in contrast with arrest at the mitotic G2/M transition, where cells continue to grow.

label.value: elongated cell with cell cycle arrest at meiotic G2/MI transition

value.value: A cell phenotype in which the cell is longer than normal, and progression through the meiotic cell cycle is arrested at the G2/MI phase transition. A cell can elongate when arrested at the G2/MI transition if it overcomes the growth arrest that usually occurs.

label.value: increased transcription during cell cycle arrest at meiotic G2/MI transition

value.value: A cellular process phenotype in which transcription occurs to a greater extent than normal when the meiotic cell cycle is arrested at the G2/MI phase transition. All genes, or a specific subset of genes, may be affected.

label.value: increased macroautophagy during vegetative growth

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the occurrence of macroautophagy is increased.

label.value: abolished hyphal growth

value.value: A phenotype in which hyphal growth does not occur.

label.value: normal hyphal growth

value.value: A phenotype in which hyphal growth is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type).

label.value: RNA absent from cell during cellular response to magnesium starvation

value.value: A cell phenotype in which the amount of RNA measured in a cell when the cell is subject to magnesium starvation is lower than normal. Total RNA or a specific RNA may be affected.

label.value: loss of viability upon magnesium starvation

value.value: A cell population phenotype in which a smaller than normal proportion of cells in the population remains viable when cells the population are subject to magnesium starvation.

label.value: delayed onset of increase in RNA level during cellular response to oxidative stress

value.value: A cell phenotype in which an increase in RNA level that occurs as part of a cellular response to oxidative stress begins later than normal. Total RNA or a specific RNA, such as the mRNA transcribed from a gene of interest, may be affected.

label.value: RNA absent from cell during cellular response to oxidative stress

value.value: A cell phenotype in which the amount of RNA measured in a cell during a cellular response to oxidative stress is lower than normal. Total RNA or a specific RNA may be affected.

label.value: two cell divisions prior to cell cycle arrest in mitotic G1 phase without nutrient starvation

value.value: A cellular process phenotype in which progression through the mitotic cell cycle is arrested in G1 phase after the cells have undergone two rounds of cell division under nutrient-replete conditions. This arrest resembles that of wild-type cells under conditions of nitrogen starvation.

label.value: abnormal glucan 1,3-alpha-glucosidase activity

value.value: A molecular function phenotype in which the observed rate of glucan 1,3-alpha-glucosidase activity is abnormal.

label.value: decreased glucan 1,3-alpha-glucosidase activity

value.value: A molecular function phenotype in which the observed rate of glucan 1,3-alpha-glucosidase activity is decreased.

label.value: increased actin filament binding

value.value: A molecular function phenotype in which the binding of a protein to one or more actin filaments occurs to a greater extent than normal. The affected protein may be encoded by the mutated gene, or by a different gene.

label.value: protein mislocalized to cell surface during vegetative growth

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which a protein that is not normally found at the cell surface is observed there.

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: abolished protein localization to endoplasmic reticulum, with protein mislocalized to cell surface

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the localization of a protein to the endoplasmic reticulum is abolished, and some of the protein is present at the cell surface instead.

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.
